post_text:
The National Weather Service has issued a Winter Storm Warning that will remain in effect from 10 p.m. this evening to 10 p.m. Monday. Forecasts call for total snow accumulations of 4-8 inches, with up to 14 inches on the benches.

Due to that warning, Jefferson Academy will conduct a late start of 10:10 for 1st-6th grades Monday morning. Because of that late start, morning kindergarten classes will be cancelled. PM kindergarten will still be held at regular times.
Write Start morning preschool is cancelled, but they will still hold Extended Kindergarten beginning at 10:10am.

In the event that weather worsens, the decision to cancel school will be made early in the morning. If that occurs, the announcement will be made by 6 a.m.

Parents are reminded that they may keep their student at home anytime they feel it is unsafe for their child to travel to school. Arrangements will then need to be made with the teacher for makeup work.

Kaysville Police Department
August 13, 2019 at 2:53 PM ¬∑

Important message for parents with students attending Snowhorse Elementary and Centennial Jr High School. Due to construction, Kaysville Police has put together a temporary route to school. The route consists of heading East on Tyler's Way and South onto Knight's Way to get to Smith Lane.

We would also like to advise that the crosswalk to Centennial Jr High School going across Sunset Drive will be in service. A crossing guard will be there to safely get the students to school.

At this time, Kaysville Police is unsure when the construction will be completed. Any questions about the construction should be directed to the Kaysville Public Works Department. They can be reached at 801-544-8112.

Jefferson Academy PTO
April 18, 2019 at 7:09 PM ¬∑

JA Families! Tomorrow is the big day...FUN RUN!!! We are so excited to see all of your students run! We are so incredibly close to meeting our goal! If we meet our goal Mrs. Jones and the PTO President will be getting silly stringed in front of the whole school. If we go above and beyond our goal the PTO will provide a school wide pizza party!

We want to thank you all for your support for this years Fun Run! We are so excited that we will be able to provide shade for the playground as well as have a field trip fund.

We look forward to seeing you all tomorrow cheering your students on! Please let us know if you have any questions!
